<L>__{interior hitchcock house, bedroom night (later)}
<A>__{hitch eases himself up and looms over alma to make sure she is safely asleep. he silently picks up her handbag and takes it to the window. using the moonlight he searches its contents. car keys. lipstick. purse. and the first few pages of a story outline: "taxi to dubrovnik" the pages vibrate in his hand as his gaze lowers to reveal the rest of the title page: "story treatment by whitfield cook & alma reville."}
